</ul>

<h4>System Support pattern</h4>
<p>The System Support role is designed for support engineers who need cross-company visibility but shouldn't have full admin power. Typical configuration: tick Companies, DB Connections, Users on the Roles tab; leave Roles, Schema Builder, and Theme unchecked so they can't escalate or re-paint the app.</p>"),

        new("promotion", "Promotion (Staging → Production)", @"
<p>Use the Admin → Promotion tab to move configuration from Staging to Production via a downloadable JSON package. No live cross-environment DB writes — admins review the file before applying.</p>

<h4>Export (on Staging)</h4>
<ol>
<li>Pick the connection schemas to bundle.</li>
<li>Optionally add notes (e.g. ""Linked to ticket #1234"").</li>
<li>Click <strong>Export selected</strong>. A JSON file downloads.</li>
</ol>

<h4>Import (on Production)</h4>
<ol>
<li>Click <strong>Choose package file…</strong> and select the JSON exported from Staging.</li>
<li>The Package summary shows source environment, exported-by, and timestamp.</li>
<li>Each entry auto-maps to a target connection by name; override any mapping that's wrong.</li>
<li>Click <strong>Apply mapped entries</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h4>Safeguards</h4>
<ul>
<li>Production refuses packages whose source environment isn't in <code>Promotion:AllowedSourceEnvironments</code> (defaults to <code>STAGING</code>).</li>
<li>Each schema config import overwrites the target's schema and writes a history row — rollback is via Schema History.</li>
<li>Reports / dashboards / master tabs aren't promotable yet; only schema configs are supported in this version.</li>
</ul>"),

        new("theme", "Theme", @"
<p>The Admin → Theme tab tunes the app's color palette. Changes apply on each user's next page load.</p>

<h4>Token groups</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surfaces</strong> — Page background, top app bar, tile/card, secondary strip (tab strips, section headers).</li>
<li><strong>Text</strong> — Primary, secondary, muted, on-toolbar.</li>
<li><strong>Borders &amp; dividers</strong> — Default, subtle.</li>
<li><strong>Accents</strong> — Primary brand color + the three semantic state colors (success, warning, error).</li>
<li><strong>Data tables</strong> — Header band, row hover, striped rows for every grid in the app.</li>
<li><strong>Master Dashboard tile chrome</strong> — Header band (title bar) and footer band (row count + freshness).</li>
<li><strong>Master Dashboard tile data grid</strong> — Sticky column-header band and sticky totals band INSIDE each tile's data table.</li>
<li><strong>Detail view group &amp; total rows</strong> — Group header band, group footer (subtotal) band, sticky grand-total band.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Picking a color</h4>
<p>Click any swatch tile to open the picker dialog. The dialog lists all 147 standard CSS named colors with a search box, an inline preview swatch, and a custom hex field for one-off values. Click a row to apply.</p>

<h4>Reset</h4>
<p>The <strong>Reset to defaults</strong> button reverts every token in the editor to the seeded values <em>without</em> saving — preview the seed palette first, then click Save if you want to commit.</p>"),

        new("tips", "Tips and Shortcuts", @"
<h4>Quick interactions</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Double-click</strong> a report name in the Builder to rename it.</li>
<li><strong>Double-click</strong> a dashboard column header to edit its label.</li>
<li><strong>Double-click</strong> a tab name on the Master Dashboard to rename it.</li>
<li><strong>Right-click</strong> a Master Dashboard tile to see the SQL that produced its data.</li>
<li>Click the <strong>Ralis logo</strong> to return to the company picker (when you have access to multiple companies).</li>
<li>Drag-and-drop reorders work on tiles, sections, column-order rows, sort dialogs, field chips, and dashboard column chips. Drop on the last item to land at the end.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Notifications &amp; feedback</h4>
<ul>
<li>Status messages (snackbars) appear in the <strong>bottom-right</strong> corner.</li>
<li>The <strong>bell icon</strong> at the top of every page tracks share + schedule notifications. Badge shows unread count.</li>
<li>Errors show user-friendly messages; the technical detail goes to server logs for admin diagnosis.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Performance</h4>
<ul>
<li>Use <strong>filters</strong> to narrow large datasets before running the query.</li>
<li>The Master Dashboard auto-refreshes after 5 minutes of inactivity — useful for kiosk-style installs.</li>
<li>If a query takes more than 8 seconds, the progress bar warns you. Past 20 seconds, it flags it as ""slow"".</li>
<li>Multi-select dropdowns are debounced — picking several items fires one query at the end.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Help icons</h4>
<p>Look for small <strong>?</strong> icons next to confusing controls (Sort By, Then By, Group By, Distinct, Scope on the Roles tab). Hover for an explanation.</p>")
    };
